. It uses plant milk, not water and its core oils are coconut oil and cocoa butter. Butta is packaged in greaseproof paper with a cardboard sleeve and uses no plastic packaging.\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>Butta ingredients:</dt>\r\n 	<dd><i></i>GMO (genetically modified organics) free</dd>\r\n 	<dd><i></i>Dairy free</dd>\r\n 	<dd><i></i>Lactose free</dd>\r\n 	<dd><i></i>Gluten free</dd>\r\n 	<dd><i></i>Palm oil free</dd>\r\n 	<dd><i></i>No Hexane</dd>\r\n 	<dd><i></i>No trans or hydrogenated fat</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n</section>&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Butta an alternative for spreading, cook and baking</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n<h2>Why will consumers buy Butta?</h2>\r\n<i></i><em>The move to plant based alternatives is one of the fastest growing lifestyles in the world.</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/whats-new/news/find-out-how-many-vegans-are-great-britain\">A study by Ipsos MORI in 2016</a> reveals that there are at least 542,000 vegans (a person who does not eat or use animal products) in Britain, three and a half times as many as there was in 2006.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ucfoodobserver.com/2015/06/04/report-un-urges-global-move-to-meat-and-dairy-free-diet/\">United Nations Environment Programme</a> highlighted the strain of agricultural products on the environment back in 2010. Consumers are becoming increasingly aware that a switch to plant based foods is required to cut gas greenhouse emissions and sustain the ever increasing population.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://thinkprogress.org/the-netherlands-new-dietary-guidelines-take-meat-off-the-menu-a97c40f05d84#.qqjmqqj68\">New dietary guidelines</a> for the Netherlands, the UK and the US take into account the environmental impact when formulating dietary recommendations promoting plant based-foods over agricultural products.\r\n\r\n<i></i><em>Consumers are choosing foods that contain natural ingredients over \'non-fat\' and \'low-fat\' varieties because they are seen as a more wholesome and healthier choice.</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.alternet.org/food/how-low-fat-foods-actually-made-america-fat\">How low-fat foods actually made America fat</a>\r\n\r\nAn article <a href=\"https://blendle.com/i/wsj-com/will-margarine-become-toast-at-unilever/bnl-wsj-20160119-SB12115899085733003306504581487633666776002?sharer=eyJ2ZXJzaW9uIjoiMSIsInVpZCI6ImFteW12YXJnYSIsIml0ZW1faWQiOiJibmwtd3NqLTIwMTYwMTE5LVNCMTIxMTU4OTkwODU3MzMwMDMzMDY1MDQ1ODE0ODc2MzM2NjY3NzYwMDIifQ%3D%3D\">in The Wallstreet Journal</a> reports butter\'s resurgence over margarine (2016)\r\n\r\n<i></i><em>Consumers are making product choices based on the overall impact of the product on the environment most importantly, sustainability.</em>\r\n\r\nOne of Butta\'s core values is to source ingredients from ethical and sustainable suppliers.\r\n\r\nThe European Margarine Association highlights the importance of sustainability <a href=\"http://imace.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/IMACE_Newsletter_lay-out-A4_MAI_v4.pdf\">as a key concept for society, business and policy makers</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.baltimoresun.com/business/bs-bz-supermarket-sustainable-food-trend-20170127-story.html\">Giant Food introduces a ratings system </a>that measures the sustainability of food.\r\n\r\n</section>&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Plant based food product sales topped $4.9B in 2016, growing 3.4% since 2015</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.spins.com/plant-based-foods-webinar/\">Spins Plant Based Foods Growth Opportunities in Retail</a>\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n<h2>Why will retailers choose Butta</h2>\r\n<i></i><em>Sales of plant based foods have outperformed all expectations</em>\r\n\r\nSainsbury\'s vegan cheeses <a href=\"http://www.sainsburysmagazine.co.uk/blog/item/10-things-you-need-to-know-about-going-vegan\">outperformed projected sales targets by 300%</a>\r\n\r\nZizzi restaurants <a href=\"https://www.thecaterer.com/articles/495103/zizzi-reports-150-increase-in-vegan-dish-sales\">reported a 150% increase in vegan dish sales.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.tidefordorganics.com/\">Tide Ford Organics</a> have revamped their range to be completely vegan.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.pret.co.uk/en-gb/little-veggie-pop-up\">Pret\'s Veggie Store</a> is so popular it is here to stay.\r\n\r\nEven <a href=\"http://www.benjerry.com/flavors/non-dairy\">Ben and Jerry\'s</a> has a non-dairy flavours.\r\n\r\n67% of consumers in the US choose plant based milks because they like the taste of it and 65% of consumers choose plant based milks because it\'s healthier than dairy.\r\n\r\n<i></i><em>As margarine sales flatten, Butta offers a plant based alternative that not only looks, tastes and behaves like dairy butter but offers all the benefits of plant based oils.</em>\r\n\r\nRetail butter compound annual growth rate (CAGR) forecast for 2015-2020 is 0.4% compared with margarine\'s -0.6%. Butta bridges the gap between the popularity of plant based foods and the resurgence in butter sales.\r\n\r\n</section>&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Vegans are inspired by health, the environment and animal welfare</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n<h2>Who is the target market for Butta</h2>\r\n<i></i><em>Millenials (born between 1977 and 2000)</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/whats-new/news/find-out-how-many-vegans-are-great-britain\">A study by Ipsos MORI in 2016</a>reveals that 42% of all vegans in the UK are between the ages of 18 and 34.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.spins.com/plant-based-foods-webinar/\">Spins Plant Based Foods Growth Opportunities in Retail</a> reports that in the US 1 in 10 millenials (born between 1977 and 2000) are vegan and vegetarian.\r\n\r\n<i></i><em>Living in urban and suburban areas</em>\r\n\r\nIn the UK 82% of all vegans live in urban and suburban areas and London contains 22% of all vegans.\r\n\r\n<i></i><em>Inspired to make vegan or vegetarian choices because of animal welfare, the environment or health</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/global/2016/sep/11/why-so-many-people-are-converting-to-veganism\">The Guardian</a> recently profiled 4 vegans and their motivation for converting to veganism\r\n\r\n</section><section>\r\n<h2>What makes Butta healthy?</h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cocoanut.png\" width=\"138\" height=\"89\" /></div>\r\n<h4>Coconut oil (28%)</h4>\r\nCoconut oil is <em>good for cholesterol</em>, its high Lauric acid content means that its energy is absorbed quickly giving a <em>satisfying</em> feeling of fullness. It also has <em>antimicrobial</em> properties which fight viruses and bacterial infections.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/canola.png\" height=\"89\" /></div>\r\n<h4>Canola oil (26%)</h4>\r\nCanola oil has the <em>lowest saturated fat</em> content of all plant oils. Its beneficial high mono-unsaturated fat content protects our heart by maintaining good cholesterol levels and it contains both <em>omega-3</em> and <em>omega-6</em> essential fatty acids.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cocoa.png\" width=\"138\" height=\"89\" /></div>\r\n<h4>Cocoa butter (21%)</h4>\r\nCocoa butter is an excellent source of natural <em>anti-oxidants</em>, omega-3 and omega-6 essential fatty acids as well as nutrients that enhance the mood and <em>immune system</em>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','About Aya for retailers','','publish','closed','closed','','aya-retail','','','2017-10-27 12:24:50','2017-10-27 12:24:50','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?page_id=146',0,'page','',0),(147,1,'2016-10-18 10:34:07','2016-10-18 10:34:07','What is Butta?\r\nButta is a plant based replacement for dairy butter; it looks and tastes just like traditional diary butter.  It has a fat content of 80% and a melting point of 25¬∞C. Butta is made up of coconut oil (27%), Canola oil (26%) and Cocoa