/?post_type=acf&#038;p=249',0,'acf','',0),(250,1,'2017-05-10 14:42:54','2017-05-10 14:42:54','<h3>My Mission</h3>\r\n<p>As a yoga teacher I share the traditional teachings of Hatha yoga,\r\nincorporating asanas, pranayama and meditation. I provide students clear\r\nalignment instructions, confrming hands on adjustments and pointings\r\ntowards meditative awareness. Together we create a loving, open space,\r\nwhere all are welcome to explore and experience the natural state.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>My Story</h3>\r\n<p>I have 8 years experience practicing yoga and meditation. I have received teaching from the Iyengar, Sivananda and Bihar Schools in yoga as well as Buddhist and Advaita teaching in Meditation . Two years ago I took a break from my job in IT and began to deepen my practice, I spent 3 months in India in a variety of retreats including 1 month in the Osho Nisarga ashram and two weeks at Himalayan Iyengar Yoga center practicing Iyengar yoga and meditation in silence. The following September I attended a silent retreat in Monte Sahaja, Portugal practicing self enquiry under the guidance of Mooji Baba. At the beginning of 2017 I decided it was my life\'s purpose to share these teachings and  returned to India to complete a 200 hour TTC at Hatha Yoga World under the guidance of Pakanj Seth.</p>\r\n<p>Currently I am taking every opportunity to teach, I spent 1 week in Africa burn and was teaching a daily drop in class at the Aliens theme camp, It was great experience teaching classes with up to 50 people. I am motivated and empowered on this new chapter of my life and have no idea what the future holds.</p>\r\n\r\n<figure>\r\n  <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/pic.jpg\" alt=\"The Pulpit Rock\">\r\n  <figcaption>Teaching a daily drop in class at Aliens Coffee, Afrika Burn, South Africa, April 2017</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n','Jon Reading','','publish','closed','closed','','jon-reading','','','2017-05-28 20:50:21','2017-05-28 20:50: