S and VEGETARIANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\nOrganic steamed coconut oil, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil , spring water, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin (vegetable fat 71%)\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup><col /><col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>How is Aya Original made?</h3>\r\n<p>The oils are melted to liquid form. Whilst cooling the oils are blended with spring water, salt and a small amount of sunflower lecithin. They are poured into moulds <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/IMG_1699-opt.png\" title=\"Moulds\"/>and set in the fridge.</p>\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p>We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the cacao from Dominican Republic. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://biona.co.uk/\">Biona</a> whose coconut oils originate from SriLanka and the Philippines. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> and originates from India.</p>\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p>Aya Original contains 10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter.  Aya Original has a total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content.  Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat. Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase your risk of heart disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aya Original contains 0.7% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable. Sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g.</p>','Products','','inherit','closed','closed','','343-revision-v1','','','2017-11-23 16:46:49','2017-11-23 16:46:49','',343,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/343-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(418,1,'2017-11-23 16:48:09','2017-11-23 16:48:09','<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\nHaving taken up a vegan lifestyle I created Aya Original in my kitchen because I didn\'t want to miss out on the enjoyment of butter and, quite frankly, margarine didn\'t cut it for me. Aya Original is made as the closest plant alternative to cow\'s butter.\r\n\r\nAya Original is made with 6 organic, non-GMO ingredients and contains no palm-oil. The plant oils in Aya Original are coconut oil, cacao butter and safflower oil. The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cacao butter is what makes Aya so melty, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. The safflower oil is cold pressed which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.\r\n\r\nAya Original is great for spreading, my favourite is on warm toast. It\'s also a great alternative to for cooking and baking.\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">