heforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(456,1,'2017-11-24 16:24:49','2017-11-24 16:24:49','<h3>Welcome</h3>\r\n<p>Yay, we\'re so excited you\'ve made it to our website!  I have a feeling that you are an individual who realises that what you choose to eat has a direct effect on your health, your overall wellbeing, the planet as well as all its beings. Congratulations, you are a conscious eater!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Freedom to choose</h3>\r\n<p>To make sure we start off on the right foot I would like to make it clear that Aya does not advocate veganism, rather we like to support vegan choices.  You could choose a vegan product like <a href=\"/aya/products\">Aya Original</a>, you could choose to have a vegan meal, a vegan day, a vegan week or even a month.  The choice is entirely yours and we hold no judgement, after all isn\'t freedom-of-choice the beauty of life?</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>For the love of food</h3>\r\n<p>Choosing plantbased food doesn\'t mean forgoing the enjoyment of food or the pleasure we get from eating.  After all <a href=\"/aya/products\">Aya Original</a> was created because the meltiness of butter is not something anyone should have to miss out on!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What\'s Aya</h3>\r\n<p>Aya is a west African Goddess of forests, she protects the forest and its animals and she teaches her tribe how to use the plants to sustain and heal themselves.  We chose the name Aya because we align with her values.</p>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-11-24 16:24:49','2017-11-24 16:24:49','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(457,1,'2017-11-24 16:26:21','2017-11-24 16:26:21','<h3>Welcome</h3>\r\n<p>Yay, we\'re so excited you\'ve made it to our website!  I have a feeling that you are an individual who realises that what you choose to eat has a direct effect on your health, your overall wellbeing, the planet as well as all its beings. Congratulations, you are a <strong>conscious eater!</st