ally when melted on warm toast :).</p>\r\n<p>Our first variety of Aya is called Aya Original, it is our replacement to cow\'s butter.  It contains cold-pressed safflower oil which is great for cooking and baking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Who is Aya</h3>\r\n<p>Aya is a west African Goddess of forests, she protects the forest and its animals and she teaches her tribe how to use the plants to sustain and heal themselves.  We chose the name Aya because we align with her values.</p>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-12-02 04:41:41','2017-12-02 04:41:41','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(499,1,'2017-12-02 04:44:25','2017-12-02 04:44:25','<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p>Aya Original our closest plantbased alternative to animal butter.  It\'s <strong>creamy</strong>, <strong>melty</strong> and has a <strong>delicious delicate</strong> flavour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ONLY ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>No PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>No GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>No DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS and VEGETARIANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p>The plant oils in Aya Original are coconut oil, cacao butter and safflower oil. The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cacao butter is what makes Aya so melty, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. The safflower oil is cold pressed which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Organic steamed coconut oil, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil , spring water, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</strong> (vegetable fat spread 71%)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup> <col /> <col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>How is Aya Original made?</h3>\r\n<p>The oils are melted to liquid form. Whilst cooling the oils are blended with spring water, salt and a small amount of sunflower lecithin. They are poured into moulds and set in the fridge. <img title=\"Moulds\" src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/IMG_1699-opt.png\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p>We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the cacao from Dominican Republic. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://biona.co.uk/\">Biona</a> whose coconut oils originate from SriLanka and the Philippines. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> and originates from India.</p>\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p>Aya Original contains 10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter. Aya Original has a total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat. Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase your risk of heart disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aya Original contains 0.7% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable. Sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g.</p>','Products','','inherit','closed','closed','','343-revision-v1','','','2017-12-02 04:44:25','2017-12-02 04:44:25','',343,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/343-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(500,1,'2017-12-05 18:11:38','2017-12-05 18:11:38','<h3>Welcome</h3>\r\n<p>Yay, we\'re so excited you\'ve made it to our website!  I have a feeling that you are an individual who understands that what you choose to eat has a direct effect on your health, your overall wellbeing, the earth and all her beings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>For the love of food</h3>\r\n<p>Choosing plantbased food doesn\'t mean forgoing the enjoyment of food or the pleasure we get from eating.  After all <a href=\"/aya/products\">Aya Original</a> was created because the meltiness of butter is not something anyone should have to miss out on!</p>\r\n<p>More than taste Aya is clean, honest and simple.  Clean because we only use organic, non-GMO ingredients which means that our ingredients are grown with organic fertilisers and pesticides and do not undergo any toxic processing.  Honest because we will always be transparent about our products ingredients, how they are made and their health risks.  Simple because the healthiest food choices are found in nature and the less processing and techniques we use the better.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is Aya</h3>\r\n<p>Aya is an authentic 100% plantbased alternative to dairy butter and spreads.  Aya is organic, contains no lactose and is GMO free.  It also contains no palm oil.  Just like butter Aya is firm at room temperature.  Aya is packaged in compostable greaseproof paper and we encourage butter dishes as a way of storing Aya in the fridge.  Aya\'s base ingredients are coconut oil and cocoa butter.  Just like chocolate, Aya is sure to improve your mood especially when melted on warm toast :).</p>\r\n<p>Our first variety of Aya is called Aya Original, it is our replacement to cow\'s butter.  It contains cold-pressed safflower oil which is great for cooking and baking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Who is Aya</h3>\r\n<p>Aya is a west African Goddess of forests, she protects the forest and its animals and she teaches her tribe how to use the plants to sustain and heal themselves.  We chose the name Aya because we align with her values.</p>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-12-05 18:11:38','2017-12-05 18:11:38','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(501,1,'2017-12-05 18:12:11','2017-12-05 18:12:11','<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p>Aya Original our closest organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter.  It\'s <strong>creamy</strong>, <strong>melty</strong> and has a <strong>delicious delicate</strong> flavour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ONLY ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>No PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>No GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>No DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS and VEGETARIANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p>The plant oils in Aya Original are coconut oil, cacao butter and safflower oil. The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cacao butter is what makes Aya so melty, it 